FIVE STARS! I don't know about you, but 2016 was awful. Just. Awful. Around July, I had been so worn-down by the year and its suckitude, I found myself to be dragging. So in the mornings, I started popping into Panera for some much needed caffeine as a little pick me up. To my surprise the staff's unwavering, cheery attitude and positive energy impacted my day more than any cappuccino could! I always leave with a smile. Working in the service industry is not easy. Working in the service industry in downtown Baltimore is downright difficult. I respect this staff for their consummate professionalism. Shout out the the breakfast crew: Laura, Yvonne, Janet, Niya, and a newcomer Sebrinna! The lunch crew is clutch too, but they normally have aprons on and I can't see their name tags very well. Thanks for making my day.  May 15, 2018- There is a new breakfast crew and they are just as wonderful. Thank you to Samone, Ebony, and Michelle, for your excellent service!
